<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Ministers of France, Germany to Visit Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 20 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine and German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel will jointly make
a visit to Bosnia on December 4, to prepare for the international
conference on the implementation of Bosnian peace agreements
signed in Dayton at the end of 1995.
</P>
<P>
"This common visit inscribes itself in the framework of the
preparation for the conference on implementing the peace
agreements which will be held on December 9 and 10 in Bonn,"
French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers of 11 countries which participated in the
Dayton peace talks on former Yugoslavia will join the conference.
Prior to that, a preparatory meeting will be held in Paris on
December 3 by officials of these countries.
</P>
<P>
During their visit, the two foreign ministers will meet with
President Alija Izetbegovic and two other members of the Bosnian
presidency, Croat Kresimir Zubak and Serbian Momcilo Krajisnik, as
well as members of the opposition parties in Bosnia, said French
and German officials.
</P>
<P>
They will also meet with the president of the Republika Srpska,
the Serbian sub-state in Bosnia, Biljana Plavsic, the
international high civil representative in Bosnia Carlos
Westendorp, and members of the Franco-German contingent serving in
the NATO Stabilization Force (SFOR) in Rajlovac, Bosnia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
