<HEADLINE> U.S. Government Science Delegation Visits Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, November 20 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. government delegation
for science and technology visited a rural energy project
in east China's Shandong Province today.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, headed by John Gibbons, assistant to
U.S. president Bill Clinton for science and technology policy,
also toured the former residence of Confucius, one of the
greatest educator in ancient China, and the temple and forest in
memory of this ancient scholar, in the company of Song Jian,
Chinese state councillor and minister in charge of the State
Science and Technology Commission.
</P>
<P>
Gibbons said that President Jiang Zemin's visit to the United
States made people to know the importance of understanding each
other's culture and history. That's why he came to the hometown of
Confucius, he added.
</P>
<P>
While in Shandong, the delegation met with Wu Guanzheng,
secretary of the provincial committee of the Communist Party of
China, and provincial governor Li Chunting on separate occasions.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the delegation attended the eighth China-U.S. Joint
Committee meeting on science and technology cooperation held in
Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
