<HEADLINE> New Russian Finance Minister Says He Needs Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Russia's newly-appointed
Finance Minister Mikhail Zadornov said today he will need a month
to familiarize himself with the job, said the Interfax news agency.
</P>
<P>
"This will be an introductory period", Zadornov told a news
conference.
</P>
<P>
"The Finance Ministry is not a simple place; I need to
familiarize myself with everything," he added.
</P>
<P>
Zadornov, who was appointed to the post by President Boris
Yeltsin today, said he had accepted the job because he hoped "to
make a difference" although this would be very difficult.
</P>
<P>
The new minister will have to relinguish his seat in the State
Duma (parliament) along with his chairmanship of the Budget
Committee, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Zadornov confirmed that the job had been proposed by Prime
Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin. He had put forward a number of
conditions before he agreed to take the job, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
