<HEADLINE> Russia Helpful in Solving Iraq Crisis: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Russia's meditation efforts
have helped pave the way for a diplomatic solution to the Iraq
weapons inspection crisis, a Russian foreign ministry spokesman
said today.
</P>
<P>
As the Gulf tension has gradually eased, he said, the United
Nations Security Council should work out more effective measures
to make Iraq more cooperative with the U.N. weapons inspection
team in the future.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, Iraq finally agreed to allow all U.N. weapons
inspectors, including Americans, to return after Iraqi Deputy
Prime Minister Tarik Aziz visited Moscow on November 18-19.
