<HEADLINE> Bottom Club Wins yet still at Bottom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Bottom club Guangdong Hongyuan
Wednesday snapped Yanbian Aodong's 10-match winning streak in a
15th round game of Chinese professional soccer league, which was
characterised by the spirited comback of relegation underdogs.
</P>
<P>
However, the 1-0 home win served only as a morale booster for
Hongyuan since they still remain at the bottom spot with a 4-2-9
record.
</P>
<P>
The second last ranked Tianjin Samsung also produced a stunning
result as they thrashed fourth-placed Qingdao Hainiu 4-0 on the
home turf.
</P>
<P>
In today's other matches, relegation-threatened August First
upset the second-ranked Beijing Guo'an 1-0 at home, Vanguards
Huandao took full advantage of home playing to down Guangzhou
Apollo 3-0.
</P>
<P>
League leaders Dalian Wanda did not have a match today as they
are competing in the Asian Club Champions League. 
</P>
