<HEADLINE> Pak Cabinet to Take Steps to Resolve Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The federal cabinet held a
special meeting here this evening, reviewing the political
situation and its adverse effects on Pakistan's economy.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet decided at the meeting, which was chaired by Prime
Minister Nawaz Sharif, to take necessary steps in accordance with
the Constitution and under the law to resolve the situation,
according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet decided to uphold the supremacy of the Parliament
and to strengthen the hands of the prime minister, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
It was decided that the matter will be placed before the
Parliament, which the sources said is confident of resolving the
crisis.  
</P>
