<DOCNO> XIE19971121.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tank Car Explosions Kill Two in Eastern German Railway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Two petrol tank cars of a train
exploded this morning in the railway station of eastern German
town of Elsterwerda, setting off a huge fire and killing at least
two persons, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
According to a police spokesman, two of the 22 tank cars in a
goods train derailed for still unknown reasons and exploded one
after another at about 6:40 this morning in the immediate
vicinity of the railway station.
</P>
<P>
A 60-year-old firefighter who rushed to the scene after the
first explosion was killed when the second tank car exploded.
Another body was found later in a nearby locomotive garage, police
said. Another nine persons were injured during the accident.
</P>
<P>
The explosions also completely destroyed the main building of
the railway station and set alight 15 cars parked outside. It took
the firefighters about three and a half hours to put the fire
under control, police said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
