<HEADLINE> New York Subway Trains Collide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, November 20 (Xinhua) -- A New York subway train
kissed another during busy hours this morning, injuring more than
75 commuters.
</P>
<P>
Sources said most injuries were minor. Even the seven people
taken to the hospitals were not suffering life-threatening injuries.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of others were treated at the scene for bumps and
bruises.
</P>
<P>
The crash happened at the Steinway Street station in the Long
Island City-Astoria area of Queens.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that an eastbound "G" train, heading from
Brooklyn to Queens, rear-ended a "R" train about 8:40 a.m. The "R"
train, which was outbound from Manhattan, was partially in the
station when it was struck, he said. Damage to the trains was
minor.
</P>
<P>
Subway service was suspended on several busy lines.  
</P>
