<HEADLINE> IDB Approves Concessional Loan for Sanitation in Honduras </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of a 13.8
million U.S. dollar concessional loan to Honduras for a pilot
program in Puerto Cortes city's water and sanitation services.
</P>
<P>
The project is to serve as a model for additional IDB lending
to the water and sanitation sector in the country.
</P>
<P>
A modern sewerage system will be built to service an estimated
56 percent of the city's 51,000 people. Presently, only about one
third of the population is connected to a sewerage system.
</P>
<P>
In the area of institutional reform, the municipal water
division will be converted into a commercial company owned by both
the municipality and the private sector.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the program is some 16.2 million dollars.
Local counterpart funds total 2.4 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
