<HEADLINE> French Troops Help Djibouti Fight Cholera </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The French troops deployed in
the Red Sea nation of Djibouti have established a medical
treatment center there to help the country fight cholera epidemic
disease, said the French Defense Ministry today.
</P>
<P>
At least six people have been killed in the Djibouti City by
cholera since November 6, when the epidemic broke out there.
</P>
<P>
It is not known whether the out-break of the epidemic is
connected with flooding in neighboring Somalia.
</P>
<P>
"Sanitary situation, plus the persistent degradation of
weather conditions, also led to the mobilization of helicopters
(of the French army) to help the people in the interior of the
country." said the defense ministry in a communique.
</P>
<P>
France has 3,200 troops deployed in Djibouti, a strategical
Arab country bordering the Red Sea. 
