<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Founder Group Comes Up With "Global Plan" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Beijing University's Founder
Group Corp, China's leading electronic publishing system supplier,
says it will increase its worldwide share with a new plan.
</P>
<P>
It announced its "Global Plan" here today for increasing
co-operation with key foreign partners in major markets to
increase global sales. As part of this move, it signed a "Software
Development and Global Co-operation Agreement" today with IBM of
the United States.
</P>
<P>
Founder and IBM agreed to co-operate as software sales agents
worldwide in the first such partnership between a Chinese and a
foreign high-tech company. IBM committed itself to selling
Founder-developed software and other products through its
worldwide distribution network, the first time for Chinese
copyrighted software products to enter the global market.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also agreed to jointly develop other software
applications in the future.
</P>
<P>
Founder President Zhang Zhaodong told the press that Founder
has made a great effort to expand its market share and has already
set up Founder (Hong Kong) Ltd., which is listed on the Hong Kong
stock market. Founder also has branches in the United States,
Canada, Japan, Singapore, and Malaysia, and nearly 500
distribution outlets nationwide.
</P>
<P>
"The partnership agreement we signed today benefits both
Founder and IBM in technical development and market expansion,"
Zhang noted.
</P>
<P>
IBM China's chairman Henry Chow said that IBM has a long-term
co-operative relation with Founder, and that more products that
meet the needs of Chinese customers are expected to be available
by using its technical expertise and Founder's marketing and
research advantages.
</P>
<P>
In related news, the State Economic and Trade Commission
reports that the Chinese government has decided to support six
major industrial enterprises, one of which is Founder, allocating
at least 20 million yuan annually for each in technology
development. The measure is meant to speed up their development
and help them join the world's top 500 industrial enterprises by
2010.
</P>
<P>
Founder Group ranked 12th among China's 120 major electronics
companies in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
