<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 21 (Xinhua) -- South Korean archers
swept the top four places in the women's event in the preliminary
stage of the 10th Asian Tournament in Langkawi, Malaysia, on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Olympic gold medallist Yun Hye Young bagged 648 points to lead
the women's 70/60m event, followed by her teammate Kang Hyun Ji
with 645 points, Hwang Jin Hae, 639 points, and Chung Chang Sook
638 points. China's He Ying was fifth with 635 points.
</P>
