<HEADLINE> Earthquake Jolts Bangladesh's Chittagong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 21 (Xinhua) -- an earthquake jolted Chittagong
city and its adjoining areas in Bangladesh late this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
According to the Seismic Observatory Center, the tremor which
started around 5:21 p.m. lasted for about 11 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Panic-stricken people, who felt the tremor like a violent jerk,
rushed out of their houses screaming. Trees and buildings were
seen tilting during the quake, the national News agency BSS
reported.
</P>
<P>
A five-story building at Hamzerlane collapsed. Fire service
personnel rushed to the spot.
</P>
<P>
The intensity and epicenter of the earthquake could not be
known immediately, BSS said.
</P>
<P>
There are no reports of casualties yet.  
</P>
</TEXT>
