<HEADLINE> New Geological Prospecting System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zou
Jiahua today called the establishment of a new geological
prospecting system adapted to the socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
Zou said that geological prospecting departments should be
fully aware of the necessity for reform and alter their
operational methods in line with national economic development.
</P>
<P>
Zou made the remarks at today's closing session of the National
Conference on Geological Prospecting.
</P>
<P>
He added that proper management of mineral resources in
different areas will guarantee the development of an orderly
geological prospecting system.
</P>
<P>
Zou said efforts will be made to explore ways for enterprises
under diverse forms of ownership to conduct commercial prospecting.
</P>
<P>
He called for expanded reform related to mineral rights, and
for the contracted use and transfer of same in accordance with the
requirements of the socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
Statistics reveal that in the past five years China has
discovered 183 energy-related deposits, with various projects
yielding an additional deposits of 3.2 billion tons of oil and
850.7 billion cu.m of natural gas. The geological industry earned
gross profits of 38.6 billion yuan in 1996. 
</P>
