<HEADLINE> HK Official: Sufficient Vacancies for Yaohan Employees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 21 (Xinhua) -- A senior official of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region said there are sufficient
vacancies for the retrenched employees of the closed nine Yaohan
Department Stores.
</P>
<P>
Commissioner for Labor Jacqueline Willis said today that the
labor Department has on its register about 18,000 live job
vacancies.
</P>
<P>
The number of laid-off Yaohan employees is 2,700. It was
announced Thursday night that Japanese chain retailer Yaohan
Department Store (HK) had applied to the High Court of Hong Kong
for its winding up because it could not pay its debts.
</P>
<P>
Willis said the department has approached major department
stores and retail chains, many of which have indicated that they
have vacancies to offer.
</P>
<P>
She added that over 2,200 Yaohan employees have made use of the
department's special centers and filled in forms for application
of ex-gratia payment from the Protection of Wages on Insolvency
Fund.
</P>
<P>
The Labor Department will continue to make various efforts to
assist Yaohan employees, she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
