<HEADLINE> Chunlan Group Purchases Leading Auto Plant in Nanjing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, November 21 (Xinhua) -- The Chunlan Group, China's
air-conditioner manufacturer giant, finalized the purchase of an
automotive plant today in Nanjing, capital of East China's Jiangsu
Province.
</P>
<P>
The Nanjing Dongfeng Auto Co., formerly one of the largest
industrial firms in a neighboring city, is now the automobile
manufacturing arm of Chunlan, a state-owned enterprise group based
in Nanjing.
</P>
<P>
Nanjing Chunlan Auto Ltd., a Chunlan holding company, has
regustered capital of 720 million yuan, including 540 million
provided by the parent company and the remainder by the former
Nanjing Dongfeng Auto Company. The new venture will specialize in
the manufacture of high-class trucks and minibuses.
</P>
<P>
In addition to air-conditioners, Chunlan's product mix includes
refrigerators, washing machines, motorcycles and automobiles.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu Vice-Governor Chen Biting said that Chunlan's
acquisition of the auto plant represents a giant step forward in
the province's reform of enterprise ownership, and will greatly
promote the local automotive industry.  
</P>
