<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Consumer Price Indices Slightly Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's composite
consumer price index showed a year-on-year increase of 5.7 percent
in October, slightly higher than that of 5.6 percent in September,
according to official statistics released today.
</P>
<P>
Analyzed by component, faster year-on-year rates of price
increase than the overall average in October were recorded for
housing, clothing and footwear.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, those components with slower year-on-year rates of
price increase than the overall average were durable goods,
miscellaneous services, food, fuel, transport and some others.
</P>
<P>
Taking the first 10 months of the year together, the increase
of composite consumer price index was 5.9 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
