<HEADLINE> Mongolia Sees Vast Potential for Animal Husbandry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia has 125 million
hectares of pastureland that can be utilized for animal husbandry,
a recent survey said today.
</P>
<P>
With a grant from the Asian Development Bank, the government
conducted a nationwide survey on livestock production, based on
which a plan will be drawn to promote sustainable development.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the country's pastureland can support 30
percent more livestock if grazing is rotated on divided
zones. Mongolia now has 30 million head domestic animals. 
</P>
