<HEADLINE> Slovakia's Foreign Debt Soars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Slovakia's foreign debt totaled
9.4 billion U.S. dollars at the end of July, a state bank
spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
He said that foreign debt is expected to be equivalent to 50
percent of the country's gross domestic product (GdP) by the end
of the year, far exceeding the 40 percent "alert line".
</P>
<P>
Foreign debt rose more than 200 percent from the level of 3
billion dollars in 1993 when the country became independent.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the country's per capita foreign debt increased
from 562 dollars to 1,700 dollars in just four years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
