<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three More Golds for South Korea at Taekwondo Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 21 (Xinhua) -- South Korea won three more
gold medals on the third day to top gold medal tally with six at
the 13th Men's and Sixth Women's Taekwondo World Championships
here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
South Korea's defending champion Dong Wan Lee won the men's
middle weight category final, world championships debutant Eyun
Joung Woo took the women's middle weight category title and
another world championships debutant from South Korea, Eun Suk
Hwang, won the women's bantam weight category crown.
</P>
<P>
The only gold medal which eluded South Korea today was that in
the men's bantam weight category, which was won by Chinese
Taipei's Huang Chih-Hsiung, bronze-medalist at the 1995 world
championships. 
</P>
