<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two More Bridges Near Completion on Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Work on two more bridges over
Lanzhou section of the Yellow river has been expedited. Both
bridges should be operational within six months, which will bring
to 23 the number of highway and railway bridges there.
</P>
<P>
The Zhongli Yellow River Bridge is a suspension span of 310
meters. Major parts of the project have been completed and the
bridge should be in operation by the end of the year. Total
investment for the bridge from the privately owned Gansu Zhongli
Group is expected to exceed 10 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Yintan Yellow River Bridge, a cable span, is 803 meters
long and 25 meters wide. Its approaches are 23 meters wide. The
Lanzhou Economic and Technological Development Zone has invested
160 million yuan in the bridge, which is expected to become
operational in May of next year.
</P>
<P>
The Yellow river divides Lanzhou's urban area into two
parts. The northern portion has become a hot spot for economic and
technological development.
</P>
<P>
The new bridges are expected to ease the transportion
"bottleneck" at Lanzhou and promote development, officials said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
