<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Li Lanqing Visits Qinghua University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
visited Qinghua University, one of China's most prestigious
institutes of higher education, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Li, member of the standing committee of the Political Bureau of
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC),
praised the university's efforts to refurbish quarters for young
teachers.
</P>
<P>
Back at the end of last year Li visited the complex and urged
the university to upgrade housing conditions for teachers. The
university administration heeded Li's call and completed a
refurnishment project within four months. Qinghua is also
preparing to expand and redecorate another residence building.
</P>
<P>
Li said yesterday that Qinghua's successful efforts should be
introduced to other Chinese universities suffering from inadequate
housing.
</P>
<P>
He noted that housing conditions represent one of the
substantial benefits a teacher should gain from hard work. Li
added that local governments should provide greater assistance for
university housing projects.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier also watched demonstrations of a customs
inspection system for containerized goods and a televised
education system developed by the university.
</P>
<P>
He encouraged the university to become more involved in the
country's economic development, and contribute more to promoting
advanced education for people from all walks of life. 
</P>
</TEXT>
