<HEADLINE> Australia Introduces New Drugs Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, November 21 (Xinhua) -- The Australian Olympic
Committee (AOC) announced on Friday a series of hard-line new
measures designed to combat drug abuse in sport.
</P>
<P>
The new policy rules that athletes tested positive to drugs
will be imposed ranging from three months to two years long
suspension after a first offence and for life for any subsequent
offences.
</P>
<P>
AOC said it's anti-doping policy also will include people who
assisted or induced the use of drugs.
</P>
<P>
Under the new rules, Australia's 41 individual federations will
have to adopt the same penalties instead of determining the
punishments separately in the previous time. 
