Thursday was overdone as it was sparked by the 11 percent fall in
Malaysian stocks.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume was up to 288.42 million units, valued at
476.13 million Singapore dollars (297.58 million U.S. dollars).
Advances overtook declines by 190 to 170, while 254 other counters
remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Telecom was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 19.8 million units. It was followed by
Innovest Bhd which had 12.1 million shares traded. RHB Capital
Warrant99 was next with 11.07 million units changed hands.
</P>
