Local food and soft drink maker F&AMP;N and the Overseas Chinese
Banking Corporation (OCBC) Foreign shared the top spot on the
gainers' list as each of them rose by 50 cents to finish at 8.05
and 8.9 Singapore dollars respectively. The Singapore Press
Holdings (SPH) increased by 40 cents to end at 15.6 Singapore
dollars. The SPH Foreign gained 30 cents to close at 21.1
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, MISC Foreign was the biggest loser as it
declined by 98 cents to end at two Singapore dollars. NBT fell by
90 cents to close at 19.6 Singapore dollars, while GE Life lost 70
cents to finish at 11.8 Singapore dollars.  
