<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Law to Ensure Equal Employment Opportunities in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong today put into
effect a new law to protect such persons as single parents, who
are discriminated against in employment because of their family
status.
</P>
<P>
The Family Status Discrimination Ordinance (FSDO) also ensures
that such persons who have the responsibility to take care of
their family members would not be discriminated against in
education, provision of goods, facilities and services, disposal
and management of premises and activities of government.
</P>
<P>
The new law is the third ordinance in Hong Kong to guarantee
equal opportunities in employment and other areas of activities.
Hong Kong has already adopted the Sex Discrimination Ordinance and
the Disability Discrimination Ordinance.
</P>
<P>
A government spokesman said today that aggrieved persons may
seek the assistance of the Equal Opportunities Commission, which
handles complaints, conducts investigations and settles disputes.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
