<HEADLINE> 60 Kurdish Militants Killed in Northern Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Sixty militants have been
killed in northern Iraq in armed clashes between two rival
Kurdish groups of Iraq, Turkish Anatolia News Agency reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted a radio report of the Kurdistan Democratic
Party (KDP) as saying that the faction started an offensive
Sunday against its rival, Patriotic Union of Kurdistan (PUK), in
the areas of Verti, Rani and Sahisipi and has killed 30 PUK
members.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the KDP has also captured a large number
of weapons from the PUK.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a radio report of the PUK said that the group has
counterattacked the KDP forces and shot dead 30 of its members,
according to the agency.
</P>
<P>
The PUK and the KDP have been fighting each other for the
control of northern Iraq since the Gulf War in 1991 when the
Iraqi government was rendered ineffective by the allied forces to
exert influence in the region. 
</P>
