<HEADLINE> Manufacturing Production Slightly Drops in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Manufacturing production in
France, which includes industrial production but excludes energy
and agriculture, dropped by 1 percent in September as is compared
with the July-August period, said the state statistics study
center INSEE today.
</P>
<P>
However, the manufacturing production in the third trimester
this year rose by 2 percent over the previous trimester, and by
5 percent over the same period in 1996, said INSEE.
</P>
<P>
In September, the production of consumption commodities dropped
by 0.8 percent, equipments by 0.3 percent and intermediary
products, such as chemical, metallurgical and glass products, by
2.2 percent, while that of automobile industry increased by 2.7
percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the production of energy industry of France dropped
by 3.9 percent in September, while those of agriculture and food
industry rose by 1.8 percent and construction industry by 2.5
percent, said INSEE. 
</P>
</TEXT>
