<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Ten rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in the operations by
Turkish security forces in southeastern Turkey in the last two
days, an official statement said today.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule, said that Turkish government troops killed six PKK
militants in the clashes in Cudi Mountain near Sirnak province,
two in Genc town of Bingol province, one in Diyarbakir province
and one in Mardin province.
</P>
<P>
Six PKK guerrillas surrendered to the security forces in
Silopi town of Sirnak province, the statement said.
</P>
