<HEADLINE> Pak PM Unfolds New Investment Policy to Revive Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 21 (Xinhua) -- In another bid to revive the
country's slump economy, Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif
today unveiled a new investment policy focusing on creating an
investment-friendly environment.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a Business Convention held here this morning and
attended by foreign and local investors, Sharif said, "the
investment policy represents the continuation of economic reforms
process which started in February this year."
</P>
<P>
Explaining the salient features of the new Investment Policy,
Sharif said, "the essence of the policy is to keep Pakistan
attractive in international investment market by improving the
Policy Regime, offering fiscal and tariff relief and through
providing procedural and social facilitation."
</P>
<P>
"The new policy measures have been proposed in comparison with
other Asian countries and considering macro-economic scenario of
the country with main stress on the polices, incentives, and
facilitation," he said.
</P>
<P>
Under the new investment policy, important sectors of the
economy like infrastructure, housing and real estate, agriculture,
health and education have been opened up to foreign investment.
</P>
