<HEADLINE> Ghanaian Gold Dealers Against Dupery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, November 21 (Xinhua) -- The Ghanaian government has
warned gold dealers to avoid losing their money as dozens of
foreigners have been duped by Ghanaians parading themselves as
gold traders.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 60 people and companies, mostly foreigners from Europe
and Africa, have fallen victim to the fraud, according to a
government statement, quoted by a report reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Some of the victims are from Belgium, France, Germany,
Hungary, Burkina Faso, Italy, Benin, Britain and South Africa.
</P>
<P>
The value of the deals ranges from about 5,000 U.S. dollars to
12.5 million dollars, the statement said, adding that the victims
were promised non-existent gold dust, alluvial gold and gold
bars.
</P>
<P>
The government said a task force of security agencies had
begun compiling the cases to ensure the investigation and
prosecution of those involved.  
