<HEADLINE> China Resets Interest Rate Range for Insurance Premium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 21 (Xinhua) -- China's central bank, the
People's Bank of China, has issued an urgent circular resetting
the range of annual compound interest on life insurance premiums
at 4 to 6.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
As of December 1, the new insurance policies must conform to
the new regulation, the bank says.
</P>
<P>
The new rates are not retroactive.
</P>
<P>
The circular comes nearly a month after the central bank
lowered the interest rate on bank loans and deposits on October
23. 
</P>
