<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Rebel Attack in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed and two
others wounded today when about 30 suspected New People's Army
(NPA) rebels attacked a police checkpoint in Quezon province, the
central Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Jaime Karingal, Quezon provincial police director, said the
victims were three employees of the local Land Transportation
Office (LTO) and an unidentified farmer.
</P>
<P>
He said the rebels surprised the LTO personnel and several
traffic management policemen who were installing a checkpoint in a
village in Quezon province and started firing at them.
</P>
<P>
The rebels fled the area after the attack, making it difficult
for the police to pursue them, Karingal said.
</P>
<P>
NPA rebels recently launched at least three attacks on
policemen and took two police officers hostage. The government has
halted its formal peace talks with the rebel group.  
</P>
</TEXT>
