<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Comesa to Set Up Court of Justice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, November 21 (Xinhua) -- The Common Market for Eastern
and Southern Africa (COMESA) will establish a court of justice to
ensure regional economic integration within the framework of
rules governing the COMESA treaty, Times of Zambia reported
today.
</P>
<P>
This news was disclosed here Thursday by Erastus Mwencha,
acting COMESA secretary general, at a one-day meeting of the
COMESA inter-governmental committee.
</P>
<P>
Nwencha said that COMESA ministers of legal affairs and
attornies-general will meet Sunday to start the process of
establishing the court.
</P>
<P>
He added that a ministerial task force of the regional body
recently went to Europe to study how the European Community court
of justice operates.
</P>
<P>
"There are already many pending reuqests for the
interpretation of the treaty provisions, which requests the
involvement of an autonomous body such as the court," said
Mwencha.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the report of the task force will go to council
soon.
</P>
<P>
COMESA, which is based in the Zambian capital, groups 20
members and aims to achieve a free trade area by 2000 and free
movement of capital and finance and people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
