<HEADLINE> CPPCC Vice-Chairman Meets Zimbabwean Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Qian Zhengying,
vice-chairwoman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), met with Sithembiso
Nyoni, minister of state of Zimbabwe, and her party here today.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcome to Nyoni and her party, Qian briefed the
visitors on how China handles relations among reform, development
and stability, and on the status of reform of China's state-owned
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Nyoni said she is encouraged by China's achievements in
maintaining economic development and social stability.
</P>
<P>
Nyoni and her party arrived here Nov. 18 as guests of the
Chinese People's Association for Friendship with Foreign
Countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
