<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Plans to Survey Marine Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 21 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government plans
to launch a survey on the country's marine resources to ascertain
the stock for their optimum exploitation, the Ministry of
Fisheries and Livestock said here today.
</P>
<P>
"We are taking steps to launch a survey on the marine fisheries
resources as suggested in the draft Fifth Five-year (1977-2002)
Plan to exploit non-conventional and un-exploited fisheries
resources in a planned way," a ministry official stated.
</P>
<P>
There are several under-exploited and un-exploited resources in
the Bay of Bengal like sharks, tuna, sardines, herrings, squids,
cuttlefish and lobsters, according to the draft plan.
</P>
<P>
The draft document observed that these resources may be
developed by "proper resource assessment" and introduction of
appropriate technology for their development.
</P>
<P>
"Since these are renewable living resources, unlike the mineral
ones, only judicious exploitation and scientific management can
ensure maximum benefit out of them," the draft plan added.
</P>
<P>
The government plan aims at exploiting the resources and ensure
their maximum sustainable yield because of their "huge" market
value abroad, the official stated.  
</P>
</TEXT>
