<HEADLINE> Foster's Updates Facilities for its Shanghai Brewery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Foster's Brewing from
Australia, one of the world's top ten beer companies, has invested
180 million yuan (about 22.5 million U.S. dollars) to renew the
equipment of its operation in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
According to general manager Li Bo of Shanghai Foster's
Brewery, the company has had a set of fermentation equipment
imported from Holland and boosted its beer production capacity to
150 million liters, twice the previous amount.
</P>
<P>
As a world-renowned brand, Foster's is produced in eight
countries and sold in more than 130 nations and ranked third in
the world in sales.
</P>
<P>
Foster's Brewing has built foreign-funded enterprises in
Shanghai, Zhuhai and Tianjin. 
</P>
