<HEADLINE> Guangxi Autonomous Region of China Forming Sugar Conglomerate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, November 21 (Xinhua) -- The Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region in south China, the country's largest cane sugar
producer, is in the process of forming a conglomerate to handle
most of the sugar production and marketing in the region.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi has led the country in cane sugar production for four
consecutive years. In 1996, the region produced 2.35 million tons
of sugar, or one-third of China's total output.
</P>
<P>
Sugar sales brought 10 billion yuan (1.2 billion U.S. dollars)
in 1996 and generated 1.3 billion yuan in taxes for the region.
</P>
<P>
However, scattered production and poor cooperation greatly
diminished the region's market competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
The regional government has encouraged key enterprises of
its 108 sugar producers to form a Guangxi Sugar Industry Group
Co. Ltd. for comprehensive sugar production, processing, research,
information exchanges and marketing purposes.
</P>
<P>
The upcoming sugar giant will be set up as a share-holding
enterprise, according to local sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
