<HEADLINE> Largest Bulk Carrier Moving to Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, November 21 (Xinhua) -- The Bulk Transport Company
Ltd. of China's Ocean Shipping Corp. (COSCO), the world's largest
bulk carrier, will move its head office from Beijing to Tianjin at
the end of this month. The company has already been registered at
the bonded zone of Tianjin's port.
</P>
<P>
COSCO set up the carrier by drawing together bulk vessels from
other shipping companies by restructuring assets in an effort to
maintain a place in the increasingly competitive international
shipping market.
</P>
<P>
At present, it has more than 110 bulk totaling 6 million
DWT. The figure should grow to 8 million DWT by the end of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin, the largest port city in northern China, has a strong
economic base. The COSCO move is expected to be a shot in the arm
to developing the Bohai Sea rim and the northern part of
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
