<HEADLINE> German Firm to Invest in Five Projects in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 21 (Xinhua) -- The German company Bayer will
invest another 500 million marks (290 million US dollars) in China
from now to 2010, the "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
