</P>
<P>
The German company sees the increase of investment in China as
a must to tap the huge market potential in the world's most
populous nation. It fits in with the company's own globalization
strategy, Becher noted.
</P>
<P>
During the first quarter of this year, Bayer's sales in China
hit 70 million marks (389 million dollars), up 12 percent over the
same period last year. 
