<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earliest Buddhist Statues of Tibetan Origin Confirmed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Archeologists have confirmed
that three statues found in Fujian province six years ago are the
earliest examples of Tibetan Buddhism in China.
</P>
<P>
The statues were sculpted in 1291 for a general of the Yuan
Dynasty (1271-1368), who was a member of a Xixia ethnic minority
which had close relations with Tibetans.
</P>
<P>
"They are the earliest and best-preserved Tibetan Buddhist
statues ever found in China," said Wen Yucheng, a noted
archeologist and historian.
</P>
<P>
The 1.5-meter-high statues represent the three most respected
Buddhas, including Buddhism's founder Sakyamuni, who are symbols
of the past, present and future.
</P>
<P>
Archeologists said the founding will provide clues to the
studies of cultural exchanges between Tibet and China's hinterland.
</P>
<P>
Buddhism found its way into China in the first century through
several routes, including via Tibet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971121.0187 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Tightens Control of Security Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 21 (Xinhua) -- The state will strengthen its
management and control of security services, an official with the
Ministry of Public Security was quoted as saying in today's China
Daily.
</P>
<P>
Lu Zhiqiang, vice-director of the Public Order Department under
the ministry, said that a campaign aimed at standardizing the
security industry will be carried out during the next eight months.
</P>
<P>
Lu said that security service companies that do not conform to
regulations will be banned or suspended, and security personnel
who are not qualified for the job will be dismissed.
</P>
<P>
Since China's first security service appeared in Shenzhen, a
special economic zone in South China's Guangdong Province, in
1985, the service industry has developed rapidly, Lu said.
</P>
<P>
Security services are an important auxiliary method of
maintaining public order, Lu said.
</P>
<P>
Various kinds of security service facilities have helped
safeguard social security and in preventing and combating crimes,
Lu said.
</P>
<P>
To date, there are more than 1,500 security services nationwide
employing more than 250,000 people, according to Lu.
</P>
<P>
A considerable number of these companies violate rules
governing the establishment of security services, Lu said.
</P>
</TEXT>
