<HEADLINE> Gansu's Ethnic Economy Booming (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tea and timber from the southern part of the country are being
sold in the Linxia Hui Autonomous County, and more than 20,000
individual or collective processing enterprises have been
established with products sold to coastal regions and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Yugu, an ethnic group found only in Gansu Province, used to
live in the northern part of the Qilian Mountains. But in recent
years they came out of their mountain homes to perform ethnic
dances at tourist sites.
</P>
<P>
The province's Gannan Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture, one of
China's five pastoral areas, has been developing its five types of
resources: forestry, hydro-power, gold, tourism, and animal
husbandry.
</P>
<P>
The prefecture has developed more than 40,000 hectares of
agricultural grassland and a grass-processing industry has been
formed to reduce animal husbandry's reliance on the climate.
</P>
<P>
Hydro-power, mining and tourism industries have also become key
industries of the prefecture. 
</P>
