<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Gets Record Number of Overseas Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Shaanxi Province, a well-known
tourist area, played host to 466,700 overseas tourists in the
first ten months of this year, a record number for that period.
</P>
<P>
Overseas tourism earned the province the equivalent of 163
million U.S. dollars in foreign currency, an 11.6 percent rise
over the same period in 1996, local sources say.
</P>
<P>
Visitors from Taiwan, Hong Kong and Macao, and overseas Chinese
rose by 92.3 percent, 32 percent and 91.6 percent
respectively. Tourist sites have been expanded from Xi'an to
include Baoji, Yan'an and Tongchuan.
</P>
<P>
Tourism officials also attributed the boom to additional
tourist activities and improved facilities. For example, Xi'an has
built culture squares and added grassland.  
