<HEADLINE> Renowned Pepper County Reaps Good Pepper Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Jize County in north
China's Hebei Province has harvested 60 million kg of peppers and
supported its title of "Home of the Chinese Pepper", which was
granted by the Ministry of Agriculture last year.
</P>
<P>
The county started growing peppers during the Qin Dynasty
(221-207 BC) and later developed peppers for the imperial kitchen,
which were known for their flavor and nutrition.
</P>
<P>
The county government regards it as one of its few profitable
sectors. About 20,000 farmers have mastered pepper growing
techniques and skills that they learned in various training
sessions. The county also has a sales force of more than 8,000
people.
</P>
<P>
Its peppers sell not only nationwide but has also in Japan,
Singapore, the United States, and about a dozen other countries.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
