<HEADLINE> Fujian Province Improve Domestic Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, November 21 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province,
which has been a popular tourist destination for overseas
travelers, now aims to expand its domestic tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
According to a provincial tourism official, Fujian has set a
target for domestic tourism of 24 million to 31 million people
with an 14 billion yuan to 18 billion yuan (about 1.8 billion
to 2.25 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The province, hometown to many overseas Chinese, has been
ranked fourth in both the number of overseas tourists and tourism
income.
</P>
<P>
Fujian is paying more attention to its domestic tourism market
because Chinese citizens have become more prosperous and have more
interest in travel.
</P>
<P>
The official said that nearly 500 short-distance travel routes
have been available, which are suitable for tourists from
neighboring provinces and weekend travelers.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Fujian had 15 million domestic travelers with an
income of 8.3 billion yuan (about 1.03 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Places of interest in the province include Wuyi Mountains, as
well as Meizhou Island, Gulang Island and Dongshan
island. 
