villages, with a combined population of 6.5 million, in central
China's Henan Province, have said goodbye to days without
electricity.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992 the province has spent 400 million yuan on its rural
electrification program to help poverty-stricken villagers in
remote areas develop their economy, according to local officials.
</P>
