<HEADLINE> Tourism on Zhejiang's Zhoushan Islands Flourishes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Improved communications in
eastern China's Zhejiang Province has made the Zhoushan Islands an
attractive place for Chinese and foreign visitors.
</P>
<P>
According to the local tourism administration, last year
arrivals in the city of Zhoushan and its surrounding islands
reached three million.
</P>
<P>
The income from tourist services on the islands was more than
one billion yuan, accounting for 12 percent of the gross domestic
production (GDP).
</P>
<P>
The 1,300 Zhoushan Islands are rich in tourist
resources. Besides Putuo Mountain, one of four sacred Buddhist
sites in China, the city of Zhoushan has listed more than 50
tourist activities which includes bathing, surfing and fishing.
</P>
<P>
The city has set up four sightseeing zones: Putuo Mountain,
Shengsi Islands, Daishan Hill and Taohua Island.
</P>
<P>
Tourists can travel to Zhoushan any time of year now that the
city has opened seven navigation lines linking it to Shanghai,
Ningbo and Wenzhou.
</P>
<P>
In July of 1997, Zhoushan's airport at Zhujiajian also began
operations.  
</P>
