<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Experts Analyze Cultural Activities of Chinese Families </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Cultural activities have
played an important role in the lives of China's 270 million
families in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Family culture has become a key part of social activities and
it has changed from a traditional pattern to a modern style,
according to a national conference on family cultural development
held in Tianjin recently.
</P>
<P>
Experts attending the conference presented 139 academic papers
on the history, present condition, and development trend of family
culture.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that Chinese modern families have more cultural
activities such as reading books, watching video programs, singing
karaoke and holding parties.
</P>
<P>
But they warned that harmful activities in some rural and urban
families such as gambling and drugs cause serious conflicts with
social tradition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
