<HEADLINE> Central Chinese Province Planting More Trees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, November 21 (Xinhua) -- The efforts of central
China's Hunan Province to cover its barren mountains with trees
have paid off.
</P>
<P>
Since 1989, the province has planted 1.66 million hectares of
trees, 380,000 hectares of them were planted by seeding from
the air.
</P>
<P>
The province's afforestation area stands at 9.05 million
hectares, and forest coverage at 51.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Its planting of grass has speeded up in urban areas where
coverage is up 20 percent from 1989, and per capita grassy areas
up 2.53 square meters. 
</P>
