government in the second half of October, The New Light of Myanmar
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Those, who "exchanged arms for peace" in the southern, western,
northern, southeastern and coastal region command areas between
October 12 and 31, included members of the ethnic Kayin National
Union (KNU) and other outlawed armed organizations.
</P>
