<HEADLINE> Indonesian Rupiah Weakens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, November 21 (Xinhua) -- Several Southeast Asian
currencies were weakening on Thursday, sending the Indonesian
rupiah down as well, Finance Minister Mar'ie Muhammad said at the
Parliament Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah was traded in inter-bank spot markets at 3,570/3,580
per dollar, down 60 points compared with Wednesday's close of
3,510/3,520.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Jakarta stock exchange (JSX) composite index,
the main gauge for local share prices, nose-dived Thursday through
the psychological 400-point barrier to hit a four-year low.
</P>
<P>
After falling 4.27 percent Wednesday, the JSX main composite
index fell 4.7 percent Thursday, or 19.52 points, down to 396.13
points.
</P>
<P>
"It's a crash," a broker said.
</P>
<P>
Some brokers said the market responded negatively to the
announcement of Indonesia's total foreign debt of 117.3 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Stock analysts attributed the fall to regional sentiment,
investors' lack of confidence and the downward trend of corporate
earnings in the third quarter.  
</P>
