<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombo Reassures of Transaction Openness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, November 21 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has
reiterated that it adopts a policy of honesty and transparency on
transactions concerning public contracts and business.
</P>
<P>
In a news release available today, the government said that it
has taken a serious view of the fact that ministers, parliament
members and senior government officials were constantly harassed
by bidders, contractors and their commission agents who canvassed
for government contracts and business.
</P>
<P>
The government recently adopted a very clearly-defined policy
regarding honesty and transparency of transactions concerning
government projects, the release said.
</P>
<P>
The government has made it clear that all forms of canvassing
and any efforts to influence unduly decisions regarding government
tenders and projects will lead to an immediate disqualification,
the release said.
</P>
<P>
Such a bidding company will be blacklisted and serious
disciplinary action will be taken against any government authority
which encourages such canvassing.
</P>
<P>
A special unit will be set up to handle complaints of injustice
or irregularity, the release said.
</P>
<P>
All Sri Lankan and overseas institutions and individuals are
requested to act strictly in line with the guidelines defined
above, the release added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
