Hashimoto agreed during their summit meeting early this month in
Krasnoyarsk, eastern Siberia, that both sides would work to
promote bilateral economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that Japan decided to accept its guarantee for private
investment granted by 11 Russian commercial banks. The guarantee
will help carry out dozens of projects valued at more than two
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Karasin said that Russia signed the accords on mutual
protection on investments with 39 countries as well as agreements
on avoiding dual taxes with 58 countries.
</P>
<P>
The Russian-Japanese business forum, which was held here on
November 19-20, was attended by about 100 Japanese entrepreneurs,
more than 150 Russian entrepreneurs and some officials. The forum
reviewed 39 Japanese investment projects valued at 2.2 billion
U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
