<HEADLINE> Finnish President to Visit Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Finnish President Martti
Ahtisaari is to pay an official visit to Russia on November 26-27
at the invitation of Russian President Boris Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents will discuss the promotion of bilateral
economic and trade cooperation, the relationship between Russia
and the three Baltic states, cooperation around the Baltic Sea,
Russia-European Union ties, and the impact of the eastward
expansion of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization.
</P>
<P>
Ahtisaari will also meet Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin and Chairman of the Federation Council (upper house
of parliament) Yegor Stroyev. The two countries will sign an
framework agreement on export guarantees.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Ahtisaari will also attend some of the
Finland Day festivities in Moscow, Finland's biggest overseas
celebration in memory of the 80th anniversary of the Finnish
independence.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony also attracts some thousand Finns from the domains
of politics, economy, culture and business.
</P>
<P>
Finland has been devoted to advancing Russia's participation in
the European integration process since Finland join the European
Union early 1995.
</P>
<P>
Political observers here maintain that this visit will help
strengthen the two countries' bilateral ties and boost the
development of the Russia-EU relationship. 
</P>
