<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Loans for Projects in Latin America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved
today four loans totaling 318 million U.S. dollars equivalent for
four projects in Brazil, Peru and Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
A loan of some 150 million dollars will be provided for Peru's
El Nino emergency assistance project, which will finance flood
protection measures in northern coastal Peru. These preventive
measures include drought mitigation in southern Peru.
</P>
<P>
Two loans totaling 140 million dollars are earmarked for
Brazil's rural poverty alleviation projects, one in Paraiba and
another in Maranhao. These projects will help assist small
projects in the two states to finance improvements in rural water
supply, electricity, roads and bridges, sanitation, community
centers and day care centers as well as other farming projects.
</P>
<P>
The project will also support training and consultant services
and research work.
</P>
<P>
Another loan of some 28 million dollars will be used to upgrade
Venezuela's environmental management. The project will help
develop national policies, legislation, regulations, economic
incentives, and information systems to increase environmental
protection and management in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
