<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Loan for Urban Development in Senegal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank okayed today
a 75 million U.S. dollar credit for Senegal's urban development
and decentralization program.
</P>
<P>
The project will support the financial and organizational
management of municipal governments and their role vis-a-vis the
central government, provide training and fiscal reform studies for
a municipal adjustment program.
</P>
<P>
The resources will also be utilized to build and repair public
facilities, which include education and health facilities, roads,
markets, bus stations and street lighting.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be channeled through the International
Development Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessionary
lending wing for developing countries. 
