<HEADLINE> Jiang's Mexico Visit to Make History: Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Mexican Foreign Minister
Jose Angel Gurria said here today that the upcoming visit of
Chinese President Jiang Zemin to Mexico will make history in the
relations of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"We are setting the basis for what will be the relations of
China and Mexico in the next century," Gurria said, referring to
Jiang's November 30 to December 3 visit.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Gurria said the Mexican government
is greatly honored to receive a visit from President Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He said leaders of the two countries have been in close contact
in recent years and that Mexican President Ernesto Zedillo and
President Jiang Zemin have cultivated a very good personal
relationship.
</P>
<P>
In recalling the development of the two nation's bilateral
relationship, Gurria said that Mexico values its ties with China.
The two countries are now on good terms and there is no obstacle
to the development of such a relationship, he said.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated Mexico's policy that there is only one China and
that Taiwan and Tibet are part of China.
</P>
<P>
"There are some issues which Mexico has always maintained
regarding China, especially the recognition of only one China," he
said. "The Mexican position about Tibet and Taiwan has never
wavered."
</P>
<P>
He also said that Mexico supports China's bid to enter the
World Trade Organization because the organization will not be
complete if an economy as important as China is absent.
</P>
<P>
On the topic of commerce and investment, Gurria said there are
some aspects that do no reflect the importance of the economies
nor the potential they have.
</P>
<P>
He hoped the meeting of the two heads of state can help advance
the cause of commerce and the economy and promote exchanges of
entrepreneurs between the two countries.  
</P>
