<HEADLINE> WFP Official Visit Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Executive Director of the
World Food Program (WFP) Catherine Bertini said today she is
pleased with the close cooperation relations between her U.N.
agency and the Angolan government.
</P>
<P>
The visiting WFP chief made the remarks here during talks
between her and Angolan Minister of Social Relief Albino Malungo.
</P>
<P>
She said the WFP has made progress in its work in Angola whose
recipient population has reduced to 660,000 now from 2.2 million
when the civil war ended in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The WFP had provided 527,000 tons of food to Angola from 1993
to October this year, she disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Bertini further said that her organization was beginning to
shift its focus from providing emergency assistance to providing
development assistance to Angola, such as the rehabilitation of
schools, clinics and roads.
</P>
<P>
The WFP chief arrived here Wednesday to start her six-day
visit to Angola in a bid to acquaint herself with WFP's work her
and with the needs raised by Angolan leaders. 
</P>
