African charter on human and people's rights and the
establishment of an African court on human and people's rights.
</P>
<P>
The draft was also examined during the second legal experts
meeting held in Nouakchott, Mauritania in April 1997, the press
release said.
</P>
<P>
It added that the proposal for such a court was given momentum
when the assembly of heads of state and government adopted it in
June 1994. 
