the Lebanese-Israeli conflict, calling on Israel to observe the
United Nations Security Council resolutions and withdraw its
troops from south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Israel established a 1,200-square kilometer "security zone" in
south Lebanon in 1985 to protect its northern border from Lebanese
guerilla attacks.
