<HEADLINE> Canada Win Women's Ice Hockey Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Canada won the title of the
women's ice hockey tournament after beating hosts Finland 6-1 in
the finals here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Stacey Wilson scored two power-play goals while Danielle
Goyette, Jayna Hefford, Hayley Wickenheiser and Kathy McCormack
added one each.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Canada beat Finland 5-2 and 7-4 and defeated Sweden 5-2
and 5-3. Finland entered the final of the three-team tournament
after beating Sweden 5-0 and 3-2.
</P>
<P>
The victory in the tournament proved that Canada are one of the
title favorites for the Winter Olympic Games at Nagano in
February. 
</P>
</TEXT>
