<HEADLINE> Athletics Australia Forced to Drop Former East German Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, November 21 (Xinhua) -- The Athletics Australia was
forced to drop former East German national coach Ekkart Arbeit.
</P>
<P>
The Australian athletics officials decided not to employ Arbeit
as Australia's team coach in the run up to the 2000 Sydney Olympic
Games, it was announced by Sports Minister Andrew Thomson.
</P>
<P>
The Athletics Australia decided to hire Arbeit earlier this
year but the decision raised a storm of protests because Arbeit's
role in the widespread use of doping in former East Germany is not
clear.
</P>
<P>
Thomson said Athletics Australia finally backed off its
decision after a meeting late on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
