<HEADLINE> Graf Delays Date of Comeback to Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Steffi Graf, the former world
number one women's tennis player, announced Thursday that she
would not return to competitions on December 11 at Bremerhaven,
Germany, as orginally planned.
</P>
<P>
Graf said she would delay her return to action in Brisbane in
January.
</P>
<P>
Graf has not played since June when she lost to Amanda Coetzer
of South Africa in the French Open quarter-finals. She then
received a knee surgery.
</P>
<P>
Graf had three screws removed from her left knee last Monday
and does not expect too much with the WTA Tour event in Brisbane
leading up to the Australian Open in Melbourne. 
</P>
