<HEADLINE> Rahal to Quit as Oldest CART Driver </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Triple title holder Bobby
Rahal was to quit his CART driver career at the end of 1998
season, he announced on Thursday in Hilliard, the United States.
</P>
<P>
The 44-year-old is the oldest driver in the race. He said at a
press conference that he had being thinking about the retirement
in the past several months and was expected to make a final
decision by mid-1998.
</P>
<P>
Rahal, who used Goodyear tires this year, was not among the top
10 in the season-ending standings.
</P>
<P>
Rahal won his first title in CART at the Cleveland Grand Prix
of 1982 when he was in his fourth year in the race. The 12-time
top-five has clinched 23 victories in his career. 
</P>
</TEXT>
