<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Deputy FM Ends Visit to Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
KUWAIT CITY, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Deputy Foreign
 Minister Tian Zengpei left here today for Bahrain to continue his
 tour of the Gulf region.
</P>
<P>
During his three-day stay here, Tian delivered a message to the
 Kuwaiti Amir from Chinese President Jiang Zemin on ways to promote
 bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Tian arrived here Tuesday on the second leg of his Middle East
 trip which had already taken him to Turkey and will also take him
 to Bahrain, Oman and Qatar.
</P>
<P>
He was received by Kuwaiti Amir Sheikh Jaber Al-Ahmed Al-Sabah
 and Crown Prince and Prime Minister Sheikh Saad Al-Abdullah
 Al-Salem Al-Sabah. He held talks with his Kuwaiti counterpart
 Suleiman Majed Al-Shaheen.
</P>
<P>
Tian said before departure that in the message to the Kuwaiti
 Amir, the Chinese president stressed China treasures the long-term
 friendly relations between the two countries and expressed hope
 that a comprehensive cooperative relationship on the basis of
 equality and mutual interest will sustain.
</P>
<P>
He said the Kuwaiti leadership indicated that Kuwait attaches
 great importance to its ties with China and the two countries have
 the same or similar views on a wide range of international and
 regional issues.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti side hoped bilateral relations will be further
 developed in political, economic and many other fields.
</P>
<P>
In their talks, Tian and Al-Shaheen exchanged views on means of
 boosting bilateral relations and signed a Memorandum of
 Understanding on bilateral consultations between the two foreign
 ministries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
