<HEADLINE> Northern Chinese City Doing Well in Export Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The city of Baoding in
north China's Hebei province, which is mainly populated by
farmers, has made 30 million U.S. dollars in exporting farm and
sideline products this year.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, the city's agriculture sector
has used 15 million U.S. dollars in foreign investment for eight
export-oriented food processing enterprises, and the city has
established ties with many foreign food suppliers. Fifteen of the
city's counties specialize in farm products like vegetables,
strawberries, and medicinal herbs for export.
</P>
<P>
To enhance its presence on the international market, Baoding
has restructured 330 backbone breeding and food processing
enterprises to form 20 conglomerates which can handle most of the
city's export business. These conglomerates achieved a trade
volume of five billion yuan in 1996.  
</P>
