on Thursday that Washington would not be bound by any agreement
between Russia and Iraq that led to Iraqi President Saddam
Hussein's decision to permit U.N. weapons inspectors back to his
country and resume their work.
</P>
<P>
"That is an understanding between Russia and Iraq. It is not
binding on us or the U.N.. It is not something we are obligated to
in any respect," Berger told reporters at a White House news
briefing. (US-Iraq-Arms Inspections)
