<HEADLINE> World Bank Assists Armenia to Improve Education Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
approved a 15 million U.S. dollar equivalent credit which will be
used to strengthen and improve financing and management reform of
Armenia's education sector.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to fund the full implementation of the
new strategy for textbook provision, assist in targeting funds and
capacity building and support institutional policy development and
management.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank credit, which will be channeled through the
International Development Association (IDA), the concessionary
lending arm for developing countries, would finance about 63
percent of the project cost of 23.9 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Since Armenia joined the World Bank in 1992, and IDA in 1993,
IDA commitments total approximately 300 million dollars for 12
projects. 
