<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Stock market in Record Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
HARARE, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's stock market,the
 second largest stock market in Africa, today continued its
 free-fall when it lost a 668.51 points, in a record single day
 plunge, on the back of waning investor's confidence about the
 future of the economy.
</P>
<P>
Stockbrokers reiterated that the panic on the local bourse was
 a result of uncertainty over the huge payments to be made to
 former freedom veterans by the government, the threat of
 nationalisation of commercial farms for resettlement of landless
 peasants and last week's sharp devaluation of the Zimbabwe
 Dollar.
</P>
<P>
The industrial index, which is the country's economic
 barometer, fell by another all time record of 500 points on
 Wednesday. It now stands at 8,457.99.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said although the government had taken measures to
 arrest the drop in the local currency, resumption of the balance
 of payments support from the International Monetary Fund is
 crucial to further stabilize the dollar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
